This is my first Google review of Sarpino's Pizzeria. I've visited multiple locations and have become familiar with the food and service. Sarpino's is open late, which can be useful for people who work overnight. I usually order a medium spinach "build your own"  pizza which is a fine size for 2 people, or just 1 if you want leftovers. Sometimes I save money and order a calzone, which by default comes with 3 toppings. I like to get some combination of green/red peppers, spinach, feta cheese or artichoke hearts.  The greatest thing about Sarpino's is their delivery service. Some days it can be lightening fast, other days it can take up to an hour. The delivery drivers are usually great, though. There is no delivery fee and I generally make it a point to tip the driver.  Once or twice I've had delivery issues with Sarpino's, but most of my experiences have been good. I have never really had any issues with this specific location, though.
